===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|景|彡|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}. The original meaning is "shadow". The phonetic component also indicates the concept of image.

===Etymology===
Unclear. Various etymologies have been proposed:
* Cognate with {{och-l|景|image}}, {{och-l|鏡|mirror}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}), which STEDT compares to {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaaŋ-I}}, {{m|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaan-II||to shine; light; bright}};
* Cognate with {{och-l|英|brilliant; flower}} or rather its Austroasiatic comparanda, including {{cog|mkh-ban-pro|*ʔaːŋ||bright (light)}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{och-l|苑|garden}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

